definition: trophoblastic layer (attaches fertilized ovum to the uterus)/trophoderm
to grow/to nourish/to increase/to cause/juice/taste/(dialect) to spout/to spurt
to raise (animals)/to bring up (children)/to keep (pets)/to support/to give birth

sentences.english: Villi are not present. Rather, there is a proliferation of bizarre trophoblastic cells.
sentences.chinese: 絨毛不存在，明顯異型性的胚胎滋養層細胞增殖顯著。

sentences.english: The pathologist determines the histologic diagnosis of the trophoblastic disease, most importantly, if choriocarcinoma is present.
sentences.chinese: 病理學家依據組織學確診胚胎滋養層疾病。

sentences.english: P53 protein was detected mainly in the cytotrophoblast.
sentences.chinese: P53蛋白主要定位於細胞滋養層。

sentences.english: Objective To obtain human trophoblast cells suitable for future experiments by in vitro cell culture.
sentences.chinese: 目的培養符合實驗要求的人絨毛膜滋養層細胞。
